#!/bin/bash

sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade

sudo apt-get install -y ffmpeg imagemagick libwebp-dev

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg
sudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/keyrings
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/gpgkey/nodesource-repo.gpg.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/nodesource.gpg

NODE_MAJOR=20
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/nodesource.gpg] https://deb.nodesource.com/node_$NODE_MAJOR.x nodistro main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/nodesource.list

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install nodejs -y

title: Password Generator
content:
import random
import string

def generate_password(length=12):
    characters = string.ascii_letters + string.digits + string.punctuation
    password = ''.join(random.choice(characters) for _ in range(length))
    return password

# Example usage:
password_length = int(input("Enter the desired password length: "))
password = generate_password(password_length)
print("Generated password:", password)

-- Initialize turtle's starting position
local startX, startY, startZ = 0, 0, 0

-- Prompt user for dimensions
print("Enter how far the turtle should dig forward:")
local digForward = tonumber(io.read())

print("Enter how far the turtle should dig to the right:")
local digRight = tonumber(io.read())

print("Enter how far the turtle should dig up:")
local digUp = tonumber(io.read())

-- Function to check if the inventory is full
local function isInventoryFull()
    for i = 1, 16 do
        if turtle.getItemCount(i) == 0 then
            return false
        end
    end
    return true
end

-- Function to dump inventory
local function dumpInventory()
    for i = 1, 16 do
        turtle.select(i)
        turtle.drop()
    end
end

-- Function to dig forward
local function digLayerForward()
    for i = 1, digForward do
        while turtle.detect() do
            turtle.dig()
        end
        if isInventoryFull() then
            dumpInventory()
        end
        turtle.forward()
    end
end

-- Function to dig upwards
local function digLayerUp()
    for i = 1, digUp do
        while turtle.detectUp() do
            turtle.digUp()
        end
        if isInventoryFull() then
            dumpInventory()
        end
        turtle.up()
    end
end

-- Main digging function
local function digArea()
    for z = 1, digUp do
        for x = 1, digRight do
            digLayerForward()
            turtle.turnRight()
            turtle.turnRight()
            for i = 1, digForward do
                turtle.forward()
            end
            turtle.turnRight()
            turtle.turnRight()

            if x < digRight then
                turtle.turnRight()
                while turtle.detect() do
                    turtle.dig()
                end
                if isInventoryFull() then
                    dumpInventory()
                end
                turtle.forward()
                turtle.turnLeft()
            end
        end
        if z < digUp then
            digLayerUp()
        end
    end
end

-- Execute the main digging function
digArea()
